title: Graph Stress Test
author: Test Harness

scene: start
You stand at the trailhead where every path in this test begins.
choices:
- Enter the hub -> hub

scene: hub
A central clearing with many well-formed paths leading outward.
choices:
- Visit the loopback meadow -> loopback
- Step into the trap -> trap
- Approach the tangle -> multi
- Enter the library -> library
- Walk toward the good ending -> goodending
- Listen to the echo -> echo

scene: loopback
A meadow whose trails curve back the way you came.
choices:
- Return to the hub -> hub
- Continue to the good ending -> goodending

scene: goodending
The intended, reachable conclusion of the story.
choices:
- Finish the tale -> theend

scene: trap
A reachable room whose only door leads back into itself.
choices:
- Pace in a circle -> trap

scene: multi
A tangle where a loop, a broken path, and a real exit all meet.
choices:
- Spin in place -> multi
- Step through the broken archway -> nowhereland
- Escape to the good ending -> goodending

scene: library
A reading room with a misremembered route to a hidden place.
choices:
- Push the shelf marked secret room -> secretroom
- Go back to the hub -> hub

scene: hiddenvault
The vault the library meant to reach, but its tag never matched.
choices:
- Slip out to the good ending -> goodending

scene: island
A lonely island no correct path reaches, circling on itself.
choices:
- Wander the shore again -> island
- Wade toward the marsh -> marsh

scene: marsh
A sunken marsh, unreached, with a broken path and a private ending.
choices:
- Step into the void -> voidland
- Sink quietly -> theend

scene: attic
A dusty attic reachable only from the cellar, which is itself unreachable.
choices:
- Climb down to the cellar -> cellar

scene: cellar
A cellar reachable only from the attic, which is itself unreachable.
choices:
- Climb up to the attic -> attic

scene: echo
A chamber that answers itself twice before offering a way out.
choices:
- Shout once -> echo
- Shout again -> echo
- Leave through the hub -> hub
